# Accessibility: Provide Meaningful Content for Screen Readers

## Principle

Ensure all UI elements provide meaningful content for screen readers and assistive technologies. Use VisuallyHidden for accessibility instead of empty strings or missing labels.

## Guidelines

### Do This ✅

```typescript
// Good: Icon buttons with aria-label
import { ButtonIcon } from '@/components/Common/UI/Button'

const PayrollActions = ({ payroll }) => (
  <div>
    <ButtonIcon
      aria-label={`Submit payroll for ${payroll.payPeriod}`}
      onClick={() => submitPayroll(payroll.id)}
    >
      <Icon name="submit" />
    </ButtonIcon>

    <ButtonIcon
      aria-label={`Cancel payroll for ${payroll.payPeriod}`}
      onClick={() => cancelPayroll(payroll.id)}
    >
      <Icon name="cancel" />
    </ButtonIcon>
  </div>
)

// Good: Using DataView for accessible data display
import { DataView, useDataView } from '@/components/Common/DataView'

const EmployeeList = () => {
  const { columns, data } = useDataView({
    data: [
      { id: 1, name: 'Alice Johnson', amount: 5000 },
      { id: 2, name: 'Bob Smith', amount: 4500 },
    ],
    columns: [
      { key: 'name', title: 'Employee Name' },
      { key: 'amount', title: 'Pay Amount' },
    ],
    itemMenu: (employee) => (
      <ButtonIcon aria-label={`Edit ${employee.name}`}>
        <Icon name="edit" />
      </ButtonIcon>
    ),
  })

  return (
    <DataView
      label="Employee List"
      columns={columns}
      data={data}
    />
  )
}

// Good: Using VisuallyHidden for additional context
import { VisuallyHidden } from '@/components/Common/VisuallyHidden'

const EmployeeForm = () => (
  <form>
    <label htmlFor="employee-name">
      Employee Name
      <VisuallyHidden>(required)</VisuallyHidden>
    </label>
    <input
      id="employee-name"
      type="text"
      required
      aria-describedby="name-help"
    />
    <div id="name-help">
      <VisuallyHidden>Enter the employee's full legal name</VisuallyHidden>
    </div>
  </form>
)
```

### Avoid This ❌

```typescript
// Bad: Empty headers and unlabeled buttons
import { DataView, useDataView } from '@/components/Common/DataView'

const EmployeeList = () => {
  const { columns, data } = useDataView({
    data: employees,
    columns: [
      { key: 'name', title: '' }, {/* Empty title - no context */}
      { key: 'amount', title: 'Pay Amount' },
    ],
    itemMenu: (employee) => (
      <Button> {/* Use ButtonIcon instead */}
        <Icon name="edit" />
      </Button>
    ),
  })

  return <DataView label="Employees" columns={columns} data={data} />
}

// Bad: Using Button instead of IconButton, relying on title attribute
const PayrollActions = ({ payroll }) => (
  <div>
    <Button onClick={() => submitPayroll(payroll.id)}>
      <Icon name="submit" />
    </Button>

    <Button title="Cancel"> {/* Title is not read by all screen readers */}
      <Icon name="cancel" />
    </Button>
  </div>
)
```

## Key Accessibility Patterns

### Screen Reader Content

#### Use VisuallyHidden for:

- **Icon-only buttons**: Provide text description when aria-label alone isn't sufficient
- **Table headers**: Explain column purpose or sorting state
- **Form labels**: When visual label isn't sufficient
- **Status updates**: Announce state changes
- **Instructions**: Additional context for complex UI

#### Use aria-label for:

- **Interactive elements**: Buttons, links, inputs
- **Contextual actions**: Actions that need specific context
- **Icon buttons**: Preferred over combining Button + VisuallyHidden

### Form Accessibility

```typescript
// Good: Use form field components with proper labels
import { TextInputField } from '@/components/Common/Fields/TextInputField'
import { RadioGroupField } from '@/components/Common/Fields/RadioGroupField'

const EmployeeForm = () => (
  <form>
    {/* Preferred: Use label + shouldVisuallyHideLabel when you need to hide label visually
        This properly removes spacing and maintains accessibility */}
    <TextInputField
      name="employee-name"
      label="Employee Name"
      shouldVisuallyHideLabel={true}
      isRequired={true}
    />

    {/* Preferred: Use description for additional context instead of VisuallyHidden */}
    <TextInputField
      name="employee-id"
      label="Employee ID"
      description="Internal employee identifier (e.g., E12345)"
    />

    {/* Radio groups with clear labeling */}
    <RadioGroupField
      name="payType"
      label="Pay Type"
      description="Select how this employee is compensated"
      options={[
        { label: 'Hourly', value: 'hourly' },
        { label: 'Salary', value: 'salary' },
      ]}
    />
  </form>
)
```

### When to Use VisuallyHidden

Use `VisuallyHidden` sparingly, only for:

```typescript
// Good: Announce status changes
const PayrollStatus = ({ isLoading, status }) => (
  <div>
    {isLoading && (
      <div role="status" aria-live="polite">
        <VisuallyHidden>Processing payroll, please wait</VisuallyHidden>
        <Spinner />
      </div>
    )}

    {status && (
      <div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
        <VisuallyHidden>Payroll status update: </VisuallyHidden>
        {status}
      </div>
    )}
  </div>
)

// Good: Additional context when needed
const FormField = () => (
  <label>
    Email Address
    <VisuallyHidden>(required)</VisuallyHidden>
  </label>
)
```

### Loading and Status States

```typescript
// Good: Accessible loading states
const PayrollStatus = ({ isLoading, status }) => (
  <div>
    {isLoading && (
      <div role="status" aria-live="polite">
        <VisuallyHidden>Processing payroll, please wait</VisuallyHidden>
        <Spinner />
      </div>
    )}

    {status && (
      <div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
        <VisuallyHidden>Payroll status update: </VisuallyHidden>
        {status}
      </div>
    )}
  </div>
)
```

## Testing Accessibility

### Manual Testing

1. **Keyboard navigation**: Tab through all interactive elements
2. **Screen reader testing**: Use VoiceOver (Mac) or NVDA (Windows)
3. **High contrast**: Test with high contrast mode
4. **Zoom testing**: Test at 200% zoom level

### Automated Testing

- **jest-axe**: Include in component tests
- **ESLint a11y plugin**: Catch common issues
- **axe DevTools**: Browser extension for testing

## Common Patterns

### Icon Buttons

```typescript
<ButtonIcon aria-label="Close dialog">
  <Icon name="close" />
</ButtonIcon>
```

### Data Tables

```typescript
// Using SDK DataView component with accessible column headers
import { DataView, useDataView } from '@/components/Common/DataView'

const EmployeeDataView = () => {
  const { columns, data } = useDataView({
    data: employees,
    columns: [
      { key: 'name', title: 'Employee Name' },
      { key: 'amount', title: 'Pay Amount' },
    ],
  })

  return <DataView label="Employees" columns={columns} data={data} />
}
```

## Benefits

1. **Legal compliance**: Meets accessibility standards
2. **Inclusive design**: Works for all users
3. **Better UX**: Clearer interaction patterns
4. **SEO benefits**: Better semantic markup
5. **Future-proof**: Compatible with assistive technologies
